Commands
********

   A LaTeX command begins with the command name, which consists of a @{b}\ @{ub}
followed by either (a) a string of letters or (b) a single non-letter.
Arguments contained in square brackets, @{b}[]@{ub}, are optional while
arguments contained in braces, @{b}{}@{ub}, are required.

   NOTE:  LaTeX  is case sensitive.   Enter  all commands  in lower
case unless explicitly directed to do otherwise.


