\sqrt
-----

   @{b}\sqrt[root]{arg}@{ub}

   The @{b}\sqrt@{ub} command produces the square root of its argument.  The
optional argument, @{b}root@{ub}, determines what root to produce, i.e.  the
cube root of @{b}x+y@{ub} would be typed as @{b}$\sqrt[3]{x+y}$@{ub}.

   See @{"Math Formulae" Link "Math Formulae"}.

   See @{"Math Miscellany" Link "Math Miscellany"}.


@EndNode

